Driss Khalid (born 7 February 1999) is a Moroccan professional footballer who plays as a forward for Amiens SC in the French Ligue 1.


== Club career ==
Khalid is a youth international for Toulouse FC since 2011. He made his professional debut for Toulouse in a 2–0 Ligue 1 loss to Olympique de Marseille on 24 September 2017.


== International career ==
Khalid was born in France to Moroccan parents. He represented the Morocco U17s at the 2015 Montaigu Tournament.At the age of 16, Khalid also represented the Morocco U20s at the L'Alcúdia International Football Tournament in 2015, scoring three goals in his first three games. He also assisted the winner in a 3–2 friendly win over the France U20s in a friendly match on 6 September 2017.


